<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Line-height with multiple font sizes</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#propdef-line-height" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Determine if the line-height value uses the largest font size when there is more than one font size." />
        <style type="text/css">
            div
            {
                background-color: Green;
            }
            #s1
            {
                font-size: 0.5in;
            }
            #s2
            {
                font-size: 1in;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the green background is tall enough to contain all of "Filler Text".</p>
        <div>
            <span id="s1">Filler</span>
            <span id="s2">Text</span>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>